Murray n 1: British classical scholar (born in Australia) who advocated the League of Nations and the United Nations (1866-1957) [syn: {Gilbert Murray}, {George Gilbert Aime Murphy}] 2: Scottish philologist and first lexicographer of the Oxford English Dictionary (1837-1915) [syn: {James Murray}, {James Augustus Murray}, {James Augustus Henry Murray}, {Sir James Murray}, {Sir James Augustus Murray}, {Sir James Augustus Henry Murray}] 3: an southeast Australian river; flows westward and then south into the Indian Ocean at Adelaide [syn: {Murray River}]
